President Muhammadu Buhari has reacted to the death of Colonel Ahmed Usman, a former military administrator in Ondo and Oyo States. The President extended his heartfelt condolences to the family of the former military administrator. A statement signed by his Spokesman, Femi Adesina, said President Buhari avers that as a military officer, the late Colonel Usman served the nation with courage and dedication. Buhari said that Usmanâ€™s contributions to peace and unity as well as his quest for public good continued even in retirement. He prayed that Almighty Allah will repose the soul of the departed. He said his thoughts are with the government and people of Kogi State, where Usman hailed from and with friends and colleagues, as they mourn this loss.